    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-31T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-31T22:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/697a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-31T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 31, 1935—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. The President is considering the advisability of making a statement in the
                    following sense: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“At this moment when the Council of the League of Nations is assembled to
                            consider ways and means for composing by pacific means <pb facs="0835"
                                n="733" xml:id="pg_733"/> the differences that have arisen between
                            Italy and Ethiopia, I wish to voice the hope of the people and the
                            Government of the United States that an amicable solution will be found
                            and that peace will be maintained.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please inform the Foreign Office of the sense of this statement in the strictest
                    confidence and say that unless there is some element in the situation of which
                    we are not aware and which makes it desirable to delay, the statement will
                    probably be made Thursday.<note n="50" xml:id="d610fn50">August 1.</note> Will
                    however await your reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
